With her, my nonchalant, nonverbal self turns ridiculous. I find myself wanting to know more, to hear more, to understand the parts of her that don't get spoken out loud. Not to possess anything, not to take space — <span class="h-o">but just to be close enough to understand the shape of her thoughts.</span>

Even the way she exists around people — akh — it feels warm. Her presence, her voice, the way she moves through moments — I don't know why it affects me like that, it just does.

Sometimes I imagine her talking freely, just telling me random thoughts, unfiltered, not careful. <span class="h-w">And I think that's what I want most</span> — not intensity, not meaning, just something real and ongoing between two people who don't feel like strangers anymore.

And maybe that's where it stops being complicated.

<span class="h-i">Not obsession. Not limerence. Just this quiet, persistent thought that she is someone I genuinely want to understand more, step by step, without rushing whatever she is becoming.</span></div>
